  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\r\nWhen an `--initial-state` is loaded, verify that the fork in the loaded state matches the expected fork at that epoch from `ForkSchedule`.  An incorrect fork should be treated as a fatal error and the initial state not stored to the database.\r\n\r\nThis ensures that people can't accidentally use a state from pyrmont while running mainnet configuration.  Currently the state loads and they just never find any peers because the finalized root doesn't match.",
